criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  All consecutive patients undergone percutaneous revascularization, both with
             symptomatic CAD and asymptomatic, with one or more coronary vessel disease, will be
             enrolled.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Infective endocarditis;

          2. Life expectancy less than 1 year for non-cardiovascular causes;

          3. Recent cerebrovascular accident (<6 months);

          4. Inability to express informed consent;
